 bei der Lektüre begleiten und dazu beitragen, das intellektuelle Vergnügen an der Tiefe (und auch Schönheit) der „Meditationen“ noch zu steigern. Mit Beiträgen von: Lilli Alanen, Gary Hatfield, Andreas Hüttemann, Andreas Kemmerling, Tobias Rosefeldt, Andreas Schmidt und Hans-Peter Schütt.  aResponses to the Meditations, a landmark work in the history of Western philosophy, demonstrate what philosophical thinking is and how it operates. This commentary hopes to guide the reader and further enhance the intellectual enjoyment of the depth (and beauty) of the Meditations. This revised second edition features an expanded bibliography.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aDescartes, René. 4aErkenntnistheorie. 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aRationalismus. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aDescartes.  aEpistemology.  aRationalism.1 aAlanen, Lilli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHatfield, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHüttemann, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKemmerling, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKemmerling, Andreas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPerler, Dominik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosefeldt, Tobias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmidt, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchütt, Hans-Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook pa